# Irregular verbs

-kula : eat
exception neg 1 sing present sili
exception neg 2 sing present huli
exception neg 3 sing present hali
exception neg 1 plur present hutuli
exception neg 2 plur present hamli
exception neg 3 plur present hawali
exception neg 1 sing past sikula
exception neg 2 sing past hukula
exception neg 3 sing past hakula
exception neg 1 plur past hatukula
exception neg 2 plur past hamkula
exception neg 3 plur past hawakula

-kuwa : be
exception pos 1 sing present ni
exception pos 2 sing present ni
exception pos 3 sing present ni
exception pos 1 plur present ni
exception pos 2 plur present ni
exception pos 3 plur present ni
exception neg 1 sing present si
exception neg 2 sing present si
exception neg 3 sing present si
exception neg 1 plur present si
exception neg 2 plur present si
exception neg 3 plur present si




#kuiva- v. to ripen
#kuja- v. to come
#kujaa- v. to be full
#kulea- v. to care for, raise (children)
#kumeza- v. to swallow up, to engulf
#kumwaga- v. to empty, to spill, to pour out
#kunusa- v. to smell
#kunywa- v. to drink
#kuokoa- v. to save, to rescue
#kuonja- v. to taste, to savor
#kupaa- v. 1. to scrape off, 2. to rise, ascend, 3. to transfer embers
#kupaka- v. to smear, to spread, to apply
#kupunguza- v. to decrease, reduce, lessen
#kuuma- v. to ache, to hurt
#kuuma- v. to bite, to sting
#kuvunja- v. to break
#kwenda- v. to go
#kwisha- v. to cease
